‐---------------------------------------------------------------

Start from file to offset, till sector conversion


From FILE → OFFSET → BLOCKS → SECTOR (no extra noise)

📦 Flow: File → Offset → Sector
[1] File (opened by user)
   file.txt

   │
   ▼
[2] File Offset
   → "Where to read from?"
   Example:
   offset = 8192 bytes

   │
   ▼
[3] Logical Block (filesystem view)
   → Divide by block size

   block_size = 4096 (4KB)

   logical_block = offset / block_size
                 = 8192 / 4096
                 = 2

   │
   ▼
[4] Physical Block (disk location)
   → Filesystem maps it

   logical_block 2 → physical_block 1000

   │
   ▼
[5] Sector Conversion (⭐ important)
   → Convert block → sector

   sector_size = 512 bytes
   block_size  = 4096 bytes

   sectors_per_block = 4096 / 512 = 8

   sector = physical_block × sectors_per_block
          = 1000 × 8
          = 8000

   │
   ▼
[6] Final Result
   → Read from SECTOR 8000
🧠 Clean Formula View
offset
  ↓
logical_block = offset / block_size
  ↓
physical_block = mapping(logical_block)
  ↓
sector = physical_block × (block_size / sector_size)
⚡ Ultra Simple Line
File → Offset → Logical Block → Physical Block → Sector
🔥 Key Understanding
Offset → byte position in file

Logical block → chunk inside file

Physical block → where filesystem stored it

Sector → what disk actually understands

🎯 Who does what?
Offset → Logical block → Filesystem

Logical → Physical → Filesystem

Physical → Sector → Block Layer

🚀 Final Intuition
👉 By the time request reaches disk:

Disk only sees:
"Read sector 8000"
It has no idea about file, offset, or blocks